external_knowledge:
- The "most highly-rated" refers to the top 10 movies with the highest average user ratings;
- "Box office performance" is considered by including the cumulative earnings of each movie, with the highest earnings for each movie being selected;
- The release year is derived from the date of the highest cumulative earnings.

- 'Top-performing movie genres' refers to genres with the highest total worldwide earnings;
- 'Average revenue' is calculated by summing the total revenue of the top-grossing genres and dividing by the number of such genres;
- 'Overall average rating' is the mean rating given by users across all movies.

- "reigns supreme" refers to the genre with the highest rank based on average worldwide earnings;
- "standing tall" metaphorically represents the genre with the top average earnings;
- "box office success" refers to the worldwide earnings of movies.

- The "global box office" refers to the total worldwide earnings of movies;
- "Reaped the most" implies the highest total earnings;
- Genres are categorized based on the `genre_name` column;
- Earnings include domestic and foreign box office earnings.

- 'Highly rated' refers to movies with an average rating higher than the overall average rating of all movies;
- 'Top-performing genre' means the genre's average earnings are above the average earnings of all genres;
- 'Outshines its peers' indicates the movie ranks within the top 5 in its genre based on worldwide earnings;
- 'Highest-grossing' refers to the movie with the highest worldwide earnings.

- "blossomed with at least 5 reviews" refers to movies that have received 5 or more reviews;
- "average rating of 4 or more" means the average rating is 4 or higher;
- "total earnings" are the sum of the daily earnings from the box office performance.

- 'Average earnings' refers to the mean worldwide box office earnings for movies in each genre;
- 'Cumulative earnings' refers to the total earnings accumulated over the years for each genre;
- 'Top-earning movie' is the movie with the highest worldwide earnings in each genre.

- "top-earning movies" refers to the movies with the highest cumulative earnings for each year;
- "shine brightly" is a metaphor for being the most successful or prominent;
- "annual constellations" is a metaphor for the yearly groups of movies.

- "Top-rated" refers to the movie with the highest average rating in each year;
- "Worldwide earnings" include both domestic and foreign earnings;
- "Genre" is a category of film or video content;
- "Total earnings of movies in that genre and year" refers to the sum of worldwide earnings for all movies in the same genre and year.

- "Top 5" refers to the top 5 movies based on worldwide earnings;
- "High user rating" means an average rating greater than 4;
- "Last decade" refers to the years between 2010 and 2020;
- "Action movies" are those that belong to the 'Action' genre.

- "reigns supreme" refers to the highest-earning genre;
- "shining like a star in the night sky" is a metaphor for standing out or being the best;
- "global box office" refers to worldwide earnings.

- "Highly-rated movie" refers to movies with a high average rating;
- "More than 10 reviews" ensures that the movie has a sufficient number of reviews to be considered reliable;
- "All regions" includes worldwide, domestic, and foreign earnings.

- "The last decade" refers to the years between 2010 and 2020;
- "Films" and "movies" are used interchangeably;
- "Run longer" implies a runtime greater than the average runtime.

- "Top-rated movies" refers to the movies with the highest average ratings;
- The average rating is calculated by averaging all the user ratings for each movie;
- The results are limited to the top 10 movies.
